Feature: Navigation Bar for Portfolio Website
  As a website user
  I want a navigation bar at the top of the page
  So that I can quickly navigate to different sections of the website

  Scenario: Navigation to the "About Me" section
    Given the user is on the homepage
    When the user clicks on "About Me" in the navigation bar
    Then the page should scroll to the "About Me" section

  Scenario: Navigation to the "Projects" section
    Given the user is on the homepage
    When the user clicks on "Projects" in the navigation bar
    Then the page should scroll to the "Projects" section

  Scenario: Navigation to the "Favorite Links" section
    Given the user is on the homepage
    When the user clicks on "Favorite Links" in the navigation bar
    Then the page should scroll to the "Favorite Links" section

  Scenario: Navigation to the "Embedded Media" section
    Given the user is on the homepage
    When the user clicks on "Embedded Media" in the navigation bar
    Then the page should scroll to the "Embedded Media" section

  Scenario: Sticky navigation bar
    Given the user is on any part of the website
    When they scroll up or down the page
    Then the navigation bar should remain visible at the top of the page
